Santander Sells Stake in Chilean Unit for $290 Million

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-02-16T18:26:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/banco-santander-chile-shares-sold-at-38-25-pesos-in-auction.html
  Banco Santander SA ,  Spain ’s largest
lender, sold a 1.9 percent shareholding in its Chilean unit for
about $290 million in an auction on the Santiago exchange.  The Madrid-based bank sold 3.6 billion shares in Banco
Santander Chile, the South American country’s biggest lender,
for the minimum price of 38.25 pesos each, the Santiago exchange
said in a statement that didn’t identify the buyers. The Chilean
lender’s brokerage unit handled the sale.  Santander held 77 percent of Santander Chile before today’s
transaction through Teatinos Siglo XXI Inversiones Ltda. and
Santander Chile Holding SA, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg. Teatinos Siglo XXI filed to sell the shares,
according to a document posted on Santander’s investor relations
website last month.    Banco Santander Chile  slid 0.3 percent to 38.4 pesos at
1:07 p.m. New York time in Santiago trading. The parent company
jumped 3.8 percent to 9.224 euros in Madrid.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randy Woods in Santiago at 
